<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14155">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Rowing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9737">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9737 mb-requirement-id-9738">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in rowing activities, including weather- and
        water-related hazards, and what you should do to anticipate, help
        prevent, mitigate, and respond to these hazards. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4hZgnGVo7Og" target="_blank"
          >5 Common Rowing Injuries and How To Prevent and Treat Them (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/fLdw5NBOf6g" target="_blank"
          >The Dangers of Cold Water Immersion (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/u-DQpJWCmHs?" target="_blank"
          >How To Stay Safe When Paddling (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9737 mb-requirement-id-9739">
        (b) Review prevention, symptoms, and first-aid treatment for the
        following injuries or illnesses that can occur while rowing: blisters,
        hypothermia, heat-related illnesses, dehydration, sunburn, sprains, and
        strains. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://paddlingmag.com/skills/how-to-prevent-and-treat-blisters/"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Prevent and Treat Blisters (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Kr2ouLj1oW0" target="_blank"
          >OSHA Heat Illness Prevention Campaign (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EmNieKLjmH4" target="_blank"
          >What Happens if You Don't Drink Enough Water? Signs of Dehydration +
          4 Ways To Keep Hydrated (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Rz6Wxiv4aRA" target="_blank"
          >Mayo Clinic Minute—Dangers of Heat-Related Illnesses (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9aFm087_XWg" target="_blank"
          >What Causes Sunburns? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/hte5VYbRXJw" target="_blank"
          >Sprain or Strain: What To Do (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9737 mb-requirement-id-9740">
        (c) Review the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy. Explain to your
        counselor how this applies to rowing activities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9753">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Before completing requirements 4, 5, 6, and 7, successfully complete the
      Scouting America swimmer test. <b><br /><br />Note:</b> See the
      <i>Swimming</i> merit badge pamphlet for details about the Scouting
      America swimmer test. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Swimming.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        ><i>Swimming</i> Merit Badge Pamphlet (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9754">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Review the characteristics of life jackets most appropriate for rowing and
      why one must always be worn while rowing. Then demonstrate how to select
      and fit a life jacket. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/4y9XPNy1L1U" target="_blank"
        >How To Choose the Right Life Jacket (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9741">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9741 mb-requirement-id-9742">
        (a) Alone or with a passenger, do the following in either a fixed-seat
        or sliding-seat rowboat:
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9742 mb-requirement-id-9743">
        (1) Launch.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9742 mb-requirement-id-9744">
        (2) Row in a straight line for 100 yards. Stop, pivot, and return to the
        starting point. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4TrFtUbat8g" target="_blank"
          >How To Row Properly (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4j0LFyrJqh8" target="_blank"
          >Rowing Technique: Mastering Oar Placement for Boat Speed (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9742 mb-requirement-id-9745">
        (3) Backwater in a straight line for 25 yards. Make a turn underway and
        return to the starting point.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9742 mb-requirement-id-9746">
        (4) Land and moor or rack your craft.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9742 mb-requirement-id-9747">
        (5) Tie the following mooring knots—clove hitch, roundturn with two
        half-hitches, bowline, Wellman's knot, and mooring hitch. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/L-SWGGN3nsM" target="_blank"
          >Essential Sailing Knots Tutorial: How To Tie Bowline, Reef Knot,
          Clove Hitch &amp; More (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EOEOAaMY_Uo" target="_blank"
          >Mooring Hitch Knot | How To Tie a Mooring Hitch (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://padutchbsa.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/04/rowing-and-sailing-knots2.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Rowing and Sailing Knots (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9741 mb-requirement-id-9748">
        (b) Participate as a rowing team member in a competitive rowing meet.
        The team may be sponsored by a school, club, or Scout unit. The meet
        must include competition between two or more teams with different
        sponsors. Complete at least 10 hours of team practice prior to the meet.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9726">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9726 mb-requirement-id-9727">
        (a) In a fixed-seat rowboat, come alongside a pier and help a passenger
        into the boat. Pull away from the pier, change positions with your
        passenger, and demonstrate sculling over the stern or side. Resume your
        rowing position, return alongside the pier, and help your passenger out
        of the boat.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9726 mb-requirement-id-9728">
        (b) In a sliding-seat rowboat, come alongside a pier and, with your
        buddy assisting you, get out onto the pier. Help your buddy into the
        boat. Reverse roles with your buddy and repeat the procedure.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9755">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Participate in a swamped boat drill including righting and stabilizing the
      craft, reboarding in deep water, and making headway. Tell why you should
      stay with a swamped boat.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9756">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Alone in a rowboat, push off from the shore or a pier. Row 20 yards to a
      swimmer. While giving instructions to the swimmer, pivot the boat so that
      the swimmer can hold on to the stern. Tow the swimmer to shore. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/7Dz4xnkbriY" target="_blank"
        >Row Rescue (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9749">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Describe the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9749 mb-requirement-id-9750">
        (a) Types of craft used in commercial, competitive, and recreational
        rowing <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vRTa7w769Rc" target="_blank"
          >8 Things to Know Before You Buy a Rowing Boat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9749 mb-requirement-id-9751">
        (b) Four common boatbuilding materials. Give some positive and negative
        points of each <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.boats.com/how-to/boat-building-construction-resin-fiberglass-cores/"
          target="_blank"
          >Boat Building Basics: Fiberglass, Resin, Composites And Cores
          (website/videos)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9749 mb-requirement-id-9752">
        (c) Types of oarlocks used in competitive and recreational rowing
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://skills.woodenboat.com/guides/oars-oarlocks-rowing"
          target="_blank"
          >Oars, Oarlocks, and Rowing (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-9729">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      Discuss the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9730">
        (a) The advantage of feathering oars while rowing <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Pz6FFr7DEto" target="_blank"
          >Squaring and Feathering an Oar in Rowing (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/P66B4GXcgO4" target="_blank"
          >Master the Perfect Rowing Technique: Feathering Explained (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9731">
        (b) Precautions regarding strong winds and heavy waves, and
        boat-handling procedures in rough water and windstorms
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9732">
        (c) How to properly fit out and maintain a boat in season, and how to
        prepare and store a boat for winter <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.boatingworld.com/question-answer/what-is-the-proper-storage-method-for-a-rowboat/"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is the Proper Storage Method for a Rowboat? (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9733">
        (d) How to determine the proper length of oars <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LPBYJS0G6xE" target="_blank"
          >Oar Length and Adjustment (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9734">
        (e) The differences between fixed-seat and sliding-seat rowing
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9735">
        (f) The different meanings of the term <em>sculling</em> in fixed- and
        sliding-seat rowing
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-9729 mb-requirement-id-9736">
        (g) The health benefits from rowing for exercise <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://biologyinsights.com/why-is-rowing-good-for-you-the-full-body-benefits/"
          target="_blank"
          >Why Is Rowing Good for You? The Full-Body Benefits (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/01CU5zQCNPc" target="_blank"
          >Scenic Rowing: Stunning Loch Lubnaig in Scotland (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
